{
  "texts": [
    "But this only shows that certain movements describable as manipulations of the laces is a necessary causal antecedent to subsequent similarly describable movements.",
    "10 For Davidson, the availability of the 'trick' underlines the threefold separation of intention, agential movement and non-agential consequences.",
    "The movements, whether in their normal shoe-and-lacesinvolving context or in the unusual context of showing it off to friends as a trick are the same type of movement, although they can be differently described in the two cases.",
    "In either case, the token of this type is the action that the agent does.",
    "The lynchpin of this argument is the A-D Principle's requirement that what an agent does be identified with some event that is attributable to her as an action."
  ]
}